There is no need to use the un-parenthesed form - it is a syntactic short form and the full form can always be used. This may make the code generation easier and have less at risk of misalignment.
```
SELECT * {
       VALUES (?x) { (1) (2) (3) }
       }
```
The query formatter does much the same - if it one variable, it uses the short form, but it does not worry about the data being mis aligned:

It is the case of (illegal) `VALUES ?x { (1 2) (3) }` becoming treated as `VALUES ?x { 1 2 3 }`.

