Thanks for the PR. I've created [JENA-1657](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JENA-1657) for this.

Was the effect to cause problems when the result data has a parse error or is truncated in someway?

You are right that the connection should be closed to catch these cases.  It's more than just `execDataset`/`execJson` - `execModel` needs it as well.

It can be done with try-with-resources.  This is done in `execAsk` - that does not seem to close the `QueryEngineHTTP` although that is mostly harmless.

To me, try-with-resources seems better because it puts all the code in one place and always closes using the language feature. `retainedConnection` is left for the `SELECT` case which streams and needs the extra machinery.

```
    private Dataset execDataset(Dataset dataset) {
        Pair<InputStream, Lang> p = execConstructWorker(datasetContentType);
        try (InputStream in = p.getLeft() ) {
            Lang lang = p.getRight() ;
            RDFDataMgr.read(dataset, in, lang);
        } catch (IOException ex) { IO.exception(ex); }
        finally { this.close(); }
        return dataset;
    }
```

